  "base_commit": "d51fb88573861e68f40d795be93101f25567b8dd",
  "pr_number": 14592,
  "issue_number": 14590,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Cross-tenant chatbot access via valid API key (`/chatbots/<dialog_id>/completions`, `/chatbots/<dialog_id>/info`)",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### RAGFlow workspace code commit ID\n\na1b2c3d4e5f67890123456789abcdef12345678\n\n### RAGFlow image version\n\n0.13.1\n\n### Other environment information\n\n```Markdown\n\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe chatbot API endpoints:\n\n- `POST /chatbots/<dialog_id>/completions`\n- `GET /chatbots/<dialog_id>/info`\n\nvalidate only that the presented bearer token exists in `APIToken`, but they do **not** verify that the requested `dialog_id` belongs to the same tenant as that token.\n\nCurrent flow (simplified):\n\n1. Route extracts bearer token and checks `APIToken.query(beta=token)`.\n2. If token exists, request is accepted.\n3. Downstream service resolves dialog globally by ID:\n   - `DialogService.get_by_id(dialog_id)` in `conversation_service.py`\n4. No tenant ownership check is enforced for `dialog_id`.\n\nAs a result, any user with a valid API key can attempt arbitrary `dialog_id` values and access or invoke chatbots outside their own tenant boundary if IDs are known/guessed/leaked.\n\n## Why this is critical\n\n- This is a **Broken Access Control / IDOR** vulnerability (OWASP Top 10 A01).\n- It can cause **cross-tenant data exposure** and unauthorized model invocation.\n- Attack complexity is low once a valid API key and a target `dialog_id` are available.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Prepare two tenants:\n   - Tenant A with API key `TOKEN_A`\n   - Tenant B with chatbot `dialog_id = DIALOG_B`\n2. Send request from Tenant A to Tenant B chatbot endpoint:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"https://<host>/chatbots/DIALOG_B/completions\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"question\":\"hello\",\"stream\":false}'\n```\n\n3. Observe that request is processed (or reaches dialog resolution) without tenant ownership rejection.\n\nThe same issue applies to:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X GET \"https://<host>/chatbots/DIALOG_B/info\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_A\"\n```\n\n## Affected code paths\n\n- `api/apps/sdk/session.py`\n  - `chatbot_completions(dialog_id)` token validation without tenant-to-dialog ownership enforcement.\n  - `chatbot_info(dialog_id)` same ownership gap.\n- `api/db/services/conversation_service.py`\n  - `async_iframe_completion(...)` calls `DialogService.get_by_id(dialog_id)` without tenant scoping.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRequests to `/chatbots/<dialog_id>/completions` and `/chatbots/<dialog_id>/info` must be authorized only when:\n\n- bearer token is valid, **and**\n- `dialog_id` belongs to the same `tenant_id` as the token.\n\nOtherwise return authorization error (e.g. 403/404-equivalent policy).\n\n```Markdown\n## Suggested fix\n\n1. In both chatbot endpoints:\n   - Resolve `tenant_id = objs[0].tenant_id` from validated token.\n   - Fetch dialog with tenant-bound query:\n     - `DialogService.query(id=dialog_id, tenant_id=tenant_id)` (or equivalent).\n   - Reject if not found / not owned by tenant.\n2. Defense in depth:\n   - Update service-layer methods (including async completion path) to require and enforce `tenant_id` when resolving dialogs.\n   - Avoid global `get_by_id(dialog_id)` in externally reachable flows.\n3. Add regression tests:\n   - Positive: same-tenant token + dialog succeeds.\n   - Negative: cross-tenant token + dialog fails for both `/completions` and `/info`.\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n- Vulnerability class: Broken Access Control (IDOR)\n- Severity recommendation: **Critical** (cross-tenant boundary bypass)\n- Exploit prerequisite: any valid API key + discoverable target `dialog_id`",
